{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772048162,"nonce":"1flzBFeEDCx8JQkx6mU88Lc3584=","title":"Support Python\u003e=3.9","message":"[Imported from GitHub #25] (created 2024-03-02T16:55:55Z)\n\nFeedbax is built on some features introduced in Python 3.11, such as [`Self`](https://peps.python.org/pep-0673/). \n\nSome users may want to use Feedbax along with some packages that do not support 3.11 yet. Ideally we would support [all active Python versions](https://devguide.python.org/versions/), though 3.8 is reaching end-of-life this year and I think we can exclude it.\n\nI intend to keep developing in 3.11, mainly because of the newer typing features. I don't foresee problems with 3.9 support, aside from the effect on typing. As for typing, I think support for 3.9 would involve simplifying some annotations, e.g. replacing with `Any` or flagging with `type: ignore`.","files":null}]}